# Pokrovka, Naumovsky Selsoviet, Sterlitamaksky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Pokrovka () is a rural locality (a village) in Naumovsky Selsoviet, Sterlitamaksky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 562 as of 2010.
Geography
It is located 10&nbsp;km from Sterlitamak, 3&nbsp;km from Naumovka.
